    "collapsible_content_JN3rhi": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can Reviv really help even if my extractions were done many years ago?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I view that the biomechanical collapse process triggered by extractions continues for decades after the procedure. <br/><br/>And so a simple mouthguard helps stop this collapse process and can reverse it.  Even many years afterwards.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tUj3HX": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "I had four bicuspids extracted before braces. Can Reviv help?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The extraction of bicuspids (premolars) is particularly damaging as the whole skull often collapses pretty significantly afterwards.<br/><br/>I do view that a mouthguard like Reviv is very helpful in a situation like this.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_6bErhk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Will Reviv re-open the gaps where my teeth were extracted?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes often as things expand and teeth move back to 'where they were', the gaps where teeth were removed will open back up.</p><p>Some folks can opt to go for implants if they want.  But I don't view that it is necessary as long as you are wearing the mouthguard at night.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jEbzGk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "I've experienced health issues since my extractions that my dentist says are unrelated - can Reviv help with these?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I've already seen a number of users report improvements in seemingly unrelated health issues that emerged after extractions.  </p><p>So I cannot promise you anything.  But I view that it is definitely a good possibility.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN",
